               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Akhlāq-i Nāṣirī by Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad, 1201-1274
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_190-item1">
                     <author key="person_12392936" ref="http://www.viaf.org/viaf/12392936/">
                        <persName type="standard" xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1201" to="1274">1201-1274</date>
                        </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1709">Akhlāq-i Nāṣirī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1709">اخلاق ناصری</title>
                     <note>Folio one, recto: a) This book was bought at Serungaputtun in July 1799 by David Price b) Note of ownership of Muhammad 'Ali c) Record of a sum of rupees. d) Note of purchase for ten rupees from Miyan Sahib on 2 Rajab 1211 (1 January 1797). front flyleaf, recto: note of valuation (of the book) 'as a gift' at 12 rupees. Back flyleaf verso: Signature of David Price in pencil, the rest of the page filled with the initials D P in pencil. This is the common later version of the work. The Akhlaq-i Nasiri is followed by a short vocabulary of Arabic words defined in Persian, written by the same scribe. Headings and punctuation in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Hamd-i bi-hadd wa thana-yi bi-'add</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 188.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Price's bequest is noted in the Journal for 1836, pp. xii-xiv (an obituary notice p. lx).</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
